TypeError: JSR package version manifest for '@b-fuze/deno-dom@0.1.56' failed to load: Requires import access to "jsr.io:443", run again with the --allow-import flag
    moduleImports = await import("./deno-wasm_bg.wasm");
```

However, if you vendorize the deps, I assume you don't expect Deno to remote-fetch a file. I wasn't sure which template to pick - whether this is a bug (probably not because the manifest is created?) or a feature request. From my POV, it feels like a bug though.

