denoland/deno#32473.body:
When using the [listr2](https://www.npmjs.com/package/listr2) npm package, since Deno 2.7.2, any console output made immediately after listr2 finishes running is overwritten. This does not happen in Node or in Deno 2.7.1.

```js
import { Listr } from "listr2";

const listrTasks = new Listr(
  [
    {
      title: "Task 1",
      task: async () => {
        await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 500));
      },
    },
  ],
);
await listrTasks.run();
console.log("All tasks completed!");
```

Correct output, as given by Deno 2.7.1 and Node:

```
✔ Task 1
All tasks completed!
```

Deno 2.7.2+ output:

```
✔ Task 1
✔ Task 1
```

I've found that this can be worked around by adding a delay after listr completes (though adding too short of a delay like 1 doesn't seem to work):

```js
await listrTasks.run();
await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 10));
console.log("All tasks completed!");
```

