denoland/deno#32780.body:
Version: Deno 2.7.5

Concurrent `node-fetch` requests through the Node compat layer cause `EventEmitter` listener leaks on sockets (`MaxListenersExceededWarning`), and eventually a response body is prematurely closed. This manifests as `"Invalid response body while trying to fetch: Premature close"` when `@google-cloud/storage` performs a JWT token exchange while other `node-fetch` requests are in flight.

Bisected to **2.6.4** — works on 2.6.3.

Further bisected to PR #31709 (see comment below)

### Reproduction

Requires a GCP service account key and a GCS bucket. Install deps: `deno add npm:@google-cloud/storage npm:node-fetch`

```typescript
import { Storage } from "@google-cloud/storage";
import nodeFetch from "node-fetch";

const bucketName = Deno.env.get("GCS_BUCKET_NAME");
const projectId = Deno.env.get("GOOGLE_PROJECT_ID") || undefined;

if (!bucketName) {
  console.error("Set GCS_BUCKET_NAME to a writable GCS bucket.");
  Deno.exit(1);
}
if (!Deno.env.get("GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS")) {
  console.error("Set GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS to a service account key JSON file.");
  Deno.exit(1);
}

console.log(`Deno ${Deno.version.deno} | bucket: ${bucketName}\n`);

// Step 1: Saturate the Node compat socket pool with concurrent node-fetch
// requests. This simulates a real app doing concurrent Google API calls
// (Gmail sync, Calendar sync, etc.) through node-fetch.
const controller = new AbortController();

async function nodeFetchLoop() {
  const urls = [
    "https://www.googleapis.com/discovery/v1/apis",
    "https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v3/certs",
    "https://gmail.googleapis.com/$discovery/rest?version=v1",
    "https://www.googleapis.com/discovery/v1/apis/calendar/v3/rest",
  ];
  let i = 0;
  while (!controller.signal.aborted) {
    try {
      const res = await nodeFetch(urls[i++ % urls.length], {
        signal: controller.signal,
      });
      await res.text();
    } catch {
      if (controller.signal.aborted) break;
    }
  }
}

console.log("Starting 15 concurrent node-fetch workers...");
const workers = Array.from({ length: 15 }, () => nodeFetchLoop());
await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 1000));

// Step 2: Trigger a GCS upload. The @google-cloud/storage library uses
// gaxios (which falls through to node-fetch in Deno since `window` is
// undefined) for the JWT token exchange at:
//   https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v4/token
//
// Under socket pool pressure from Step 1, the 200 response body from the
// token endpoint is prematurely closed before it can be read.
console.log("Uploading to GCS (triggers JWT token exchange via node-fetch)...\n");

const storage = new Storage({ projectId });
const bucket = storage.bucket(bucketName);
const file = bucket.file(`repro-test-${Date.now()}`);

try {
  await file.save(new TextEncoder().encode("test content"), {
    metadata: {
      contentType: "text/plain",
      metadata: { filename: "test.txt" },
    },
  });
  console.log("Upload succeeded — bug not reproduced.");
  await file.delete().catch(() => {});
} catch (err) {
  console.error(`REPRODUCED: ${(err as Error).message}\n`);
  console.error((err as Error).stack);
}

controller.abort();
await Promise.allSettled(workers);
```

```
$ GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=key.json GCS_BUCKET_NAME=my-bucket \
  deno run --allow-net --allow-env --allow-read repro.ts
```

Results:
  - 2.6.3: PASS (upload succeeds)
  - 2.6.4+: FAIL:
```
(node:67877) MaxListenersExceededWarning: Possible EventEmitter memory leak detected. 11 close listeners added to [Socket]. MaxListeners is 10.
(node:67877) MaxListenersExceededWarning: Possible EventEmitter memory leak detected. 11 data listeners added to [Socket]. MaxListeners is 10.
... snip ...
(node:67877) MaxListenersExceededWarning: Possible EventEmitter memory leak detected. 11 data listeners added to [Socket]. MaxListeners is 10.

Error: Invalid response body while trying to fetch https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v4/token: Premature close
```

### Symptoms

1. **Socket listener leak** (observable without credentials): concurrent `node-fetch` requests produce `MaxListenersExceededWarning: Possible EventEmitter memory leak detected. 11 close listeners added to [Socket]` — this happens on every run and does not require GCS.

2. **Premature close**: when `@google-cloud/storage`'s resumable upload triggers a JWT token exchange through the corrupted socket pool, the 200 response body stream is closed before it can be read. The full stack trace:

```
Error: Invalid response body while trying to fetch https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v4/token: Premature close
    at Gaxios._request (gaxios/build/src/gaxios.js:149:19)
    at async GoogleToken._GoogleToken_requestToken (gtoken/build/src/index.js:241:19)
    at async GoogleToken._GoogleToken_getTokenAsync (gtoken/build/src/index.js:160:16)
    at async JWT.refreshTokenNoCache (google-auth-library/build/src/auth/jwtclient.js:173:23)
    at async JWT.getRequestMetadataAsync (google-auth-library/build/src/auth/oauth2client.js:333:17)
    at async JWT.requestAsync (google-auth-library/build/src/auth/oauth2client.js:418:23)
    at async Upload.makeRequest (@google-cloud/storage/build/esm/src/resumable-upload.js:727:21)
    at async AsyncRetry.retries (@google-cloud/storage/build/esm/src/resumable-upload.js:393:29)
```

denoland/deno#32871.body:
Version: Deno 2.7.7

When running the `deno audit` command, it reported an issue with a library `flatted` that is imported as a part of the `@vitest/ui` library.  The vitest library pins the specific version of flatted to 3.4.0, so unfortunately I cannot simply import a newer `flatted` version and fix it.  

However, I tried to use the overrides tag to force the version up to the specific version (temporarily) to allow the audit command to pass, but it appears audit doesn't honor the `overrides` property.

package.json
```
{
  "devDependencies": {
    "@vitest/ui": "^4.1.0"
  },
  "overrides": {
    "flatted": "3.4.2"
  }
