Hi,

I would like to report a behavior I observed in Deno 2.7.7 
The PoC can be reproduced by following the below steps:

1. `npm install quick-lru@7.0.0`
2. Create `repro.mjs`:
```javascript
import QuickLRU from 'quick-lru';

class BotChatEmitter {}

class Bot {
  constructor() {
    this.chatEventEmitter = new BotChatEmitter();
    // Create a QuickLRU instance and store a reference to `this` (Bot)
    this.cache = new QuickLRU({ maxSize: 10 });
    this.cache.set('bot', this);
    // Also create an explicit circular reference for clarity
    this.chatEventEmitter.bot = this;
  }
}

const bot = new Bot();

// This console.log should be safe and either print the object
// or show [Circular] for circular references, but instead it
// triggers a TypeError
console.log(bot);
```
3. Run using `deno run -A repro.mjs`

#### Expected output
Should not throw any error as in the case of Node and print Circular reference as [Circular]
```
root@KContainer:~/temp/55539# node repro.mjs
<ref *1> Bot {
  chatEventEmitter: BotChatEmitter { bot: [Circular *1] },
  cache: QuickLRU(0) {}
}
